'''2009年木星撞击事件'''，又被称为'''韦斯利撞击事件'''，是2009年7月在[[木星|木星]]发生的[[撞击事件|撞击事件]]。这次撞击事件在木星大气层中留下一个黑色的疤斑，大小和木星[[木星大氣層#长圆形_BA|小红斑]]类似，面积和地球[[太平洋|太平洋]]差不多。<ref name="berkeleypr">[http://www.berkeley.edu/news/media/releases/2009/07/21_bruise.shtml Jupiter pummeled, leaving bruise the size of the Pacific Ocean] {{Wayback|url=http://www.berkeley.edu/news/media/releases/2009/07/21_bruise.shtml |date=20171201042515 }}. University of California, Berkeley press release, July 21, 2009.</ref> 科学家估计撞击物的直径约为200-500米。<ref name="PR2011"/>

== 发现 ==
此次撞击事件是由[[澳大利亚|澳大利亚]][[天文爱好者|天文爱好者]]安东尼·韦斯利（Anthony Wesley）在2009年7月19日[[协调世界时|协调世界时]]13:30（大约刚好在[[苏梅克－列维9号彗星|苏梅克－列维9号彗星]]撞击木星后15年）发现的。他在位于澳大利亚[[新南威尔士州|新南威尔士州]]穆任百特曼村郊外的家中后院天文台使用和14.5英寸（36.8厘米）口径的[[反射望远镜|反射望远镜]]连接的低光度摄像机对木星进行拍摄后叠加图片时发现这次事件。<ref>{{cite news|author=Mackey, Robert|title=Amateur Finds New Earth-Sized Blot on Jupiter|url=http://thelede.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/07/21/amateur-astronomer-finds-new-earth-size-impact-mark-on-jupiter/|date=July 21, 2009|publisher=The New York Times|accessdate=2009-07-21|archive-date=2018-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626135339/https://thelede.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/07/21/amateur-astronomer-finds-new-earth-size-impact-mark-on-jupiter/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 他回忆说：

{{quote|我第一次见到它时位于木星的边缘，只是一个模糊的暗斑，当时认为只是一个普通的木星极暴。但是，随着木星自转，斑点逐渐对向地球，观察条件变好，我突然间发现，这不只是是一个暗斑，在不同图片的通道都是黑色的，这意味着它是一个真正黑斑。<ref>{{cite web |author=Wesley, Anthony |title=Impact mark on Jupiter, 19th July 2009 |url=http://jupiter.samba.org/jupiter-impact.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5iTsIBdEs?url=http://jupiter.samba.org/jupiter-impact.html |archivedate=2009-07-23 |publisher=(jupiter.samba.org) |accessdate=2009-07-21 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>}}

韦斯利立即发送邮件给全世界的爱好者和天文机构报告这次发现，其中包括位于[[美国|美国]][[加利福尼亚州|加利福尼亚州]][[帕萨迪纳_(加利福尼亚州)|帕萨迪纳]]的[[NASA|NASA]][[喷气推进实验室|喷气推进实验室]]。<ref>{{cite news|author=O'Loughlin, Toni and agencies|title=Amateur astronomer spots Earth-size scar on Jupiter|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/science/2009/jul/21/jupiter-scar-comet-asteroid-crash|publisher=The Guardian|accessdate=2009-07-21|location=London|date=2009-07-21|archive-date=2012-04-04|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/66fish7nt?url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/science/2009/jul/21/jupiter-scar-comet-asteroid-crash|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 调查 ==
[[保罗·卡拉斯|保罗·卡拉斯]]等人证实了这次撞击事件。他们在[[夏威夷|夏威夷]][[凯克天文台|凯克天文台]]拥有观测时间，本来计划用来观测[[北落师门b|北落师门b]]，在收到消息后，他们立即挤出一定的时间观测这次木星撞击。<ref name="keckpr">[http://keckobservatory.org/index.php/news/jupiters_adds_a_feature/ Jupiter adds a feature] {{Wayback|url=http://keckobservatory.org/index.php/news/jupiters_adds_a_feature/ |date=20110720180242 }}. Keck Observatory observations, July 21, 2009</ref> 凯克天文台和NASA红外望远镜的红外观测显示在撞击位置出现一个亮斑，提示这次撞击加热了木星南极附近西经305°，南纬57°处约1.9亿平方公里的低层大气。<ref name="berkeleypr"/>

这个令人瞩目的斑痕表明它和苏梅克－列维9号彗星撞击木星事件时的发现相似，由高海拔的气雾组成。<ref name="keckpr"/> 格伦·奥顿和他的团队利用近红外和红外观测在木星的上层大气探测到明亮的上涌粒子，而使用中红外波长观测，发现可能的额外[[氨|氨]]气排放。<ref name=Martinez>{{cite web|author=Martinez, Carolina|title=New NASA Images Indicate Object Hits Jupiter|url=http://www.nasa.gov/topics/solarsystem/features/jup-20090720.html|date=July 20, 2009|publisher=Jet Propulsion Laboratory|accessdate=2009-07-21|archive-date=2009-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090727121804/http://www.nasa.gov/topics/solarsystem/features/jup-20090720.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

这次在木星的撞击事件，其爆炸的威力是1908年6月疑似彗星或小行星撞击地球的[[西伯利亚|西伯利亚]][[通古斯大爆炸|通古斯大爆炸]]的数千倍以上。<ref name="hubblesite">{{cite web |title=Hubble Captures Rare Jupiter Collision |publisher=Hubblesite (STScI-2009-23) |url=http://hubblesite.org/newscenter/archive/releases/2009/23/full |date=2009-07-24 |accessdate=2009-07-24 |archive-date=2016-08-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160804131242/http://hubblesite.org/newscenter/archive/releases/2009/23/full/ |dead-url=no }}</ref> （这比[[广岛|广岛]][[原子弹|原子弹]]爆炸的威力强大一百万倍以上）<ref>{{Cite book | last = Longo | first = Giuseppe | editor-last = Bobrowsky | editor-first = Peter T. | editor2-last = Rickman | editor2-first = Hans | title = Comet/Asteroid Impacts and Human Society, An Interdisciplinary Approach | chapter = 18 | pages = 303–330 | publisher = Springer-Verlag | place = Berlin Heidelberg New York | publication-date = 2007 | contribution-url = http://www-th.bo.infn.it/tunguska/Asteroids-Chapter-18.pdf | isbn = 3-540-32709-6 | year = 2007 | postscript = . | access-date = 2012-02-24 | archive-date = 2009-07-29 | archive-url = https://www.webcitation.org/5icderdjK?url=http://www-th.bo.infn.it/tunguska/Asteroids-Chapter-18.pdf | dead-url = yes }}. Accessed 2009-07-27.   2009-07-29.</ref>

天文学家使用凯克天文台<ref name="keckpr"/>和[[哈勃太空望远镜|哈勃太空望远镜]]在STS-125任务安装的[[第三代广域照相机|第三代广域照相机]]<ref name="berkeleypr"/>对这次撞击事件进行进一步观测。

==撞击物==
此次撞击木星的对象在韦斯利发现撞击事件前并没有被发现。不过，在2003年发表的一篇论文预测大约每90至500年木星就会遭遇一次直径大于1.5公里的[[彗星|彗星]]撞击<ref>{{Cite journal |first=Kevin |last=Zahnle |first2=Paul |last2=Schenk |first3=Harold |last3=Levison |first4=Luke |last4=Dones |year=2003 |month= |title=Cratering rates in the outer Solar System |journal=[[Icarus_(journal)|Icarus]] |volume=163 |issue=163 |pages=263–289 |url=http://lasp.colorado.edu/~espoclass/homework/5830_2008_homework/Zahnle2003CrateringRates.pdf |format=pdf |bibcode=2003Icar..163..263Z |issn= |quote=1.5-km-diameter comets is currently N(d > 1.5 km) = 0.005 +0.006 -0.003 per annum |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5icdGOsFF?url=http://lasp.colorado.edu/~espoclass/homework/5830_2008_homework/Zahnle2003CrateringRates.pdf |archivedate=2009-07-29 |deadurl=yes |accessdate=2009-07-27 |doi=10.1016/S0019-1035(03)00048-4 |postscript=. |author= }}</ref>，而在1997年的调查认为，[[乔瓦尼·多梅尼科·卡西尼|乔瓦尼·多梅尼科·卡西尼]]可能在1690年已经发现并记录过木星撞击事件。<ref>{{Cite journal |first=Isshi |last=Tabe |first2=Jun-ichi |last2=Watanabe |first3=Michiwo |last3=Jimbo |title=Discovery of a Possible Impact SPOT on Jupiter Recorded in 1690 |journal=Publ. of the Astronomical Society of Japan |volume=49 |issue= |pages=L1–L5 |bibcode=1997PASJ...49L...1T |issn= |quote=Jupiter has been continuously monitored for almost 400 yr |postscript=.|date=February 1997}}</ref>

根据苏梅克－列维9号彗星撞击体的大小计算<ref name="sl9-size">{{cite web |title=Comet Shoemaker-Levy 9 Fragment Size |publisher=Lunar and Planetary Institute |author=D. A. Crawford |url=http://www.lpi.usra.edu/meetings/lpsc97/pdf/1351.PDF |accessdate=2009-07-22 |archive-date=2020-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112011934/https://www.lpi.usra.edu/meetings/lpsc97/pdf/1351.PDF |dead-url=no }}</ref>，此次撞击物的直径可能小于1千米。<ref name="hubblesite"/><ref name="gemini">{{cite web |title=Surprise Collision on Jupiter Captured by Gemini Telescope |publisher=Gemini Observatory |url=http://www.gemini.edu/node/11300 |accessdate=2009-07-24 |archive-date=2020-11-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201122125400/http://www.gemini.edu/node/11300 |dead-url=no }}</ref><!-- <ref name="Tedmanson">{{cite news|url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/uk/science/article6721504.ece|title=Backyard astronomer discovers black spot on Jupiter|last=Tedmanson|first=Sophie|date=2009-07-22|publisher=[[The_Times|The Times]]|accessdate=2009-07-22 | location=London}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/science/space/5882014/Planet-Jupiter-hit-by-object-which-left-a-dent-the-size-of-Earth.html|title=Planet Jupiter hit by object which left a dent the size of Earth |date=2009-07-21|source=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]]|accessdate=2009-07-22 | location=London}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/idUKTRE56K0ZV20090721|title=Giant "scar" on Jupiter spotted by amateur stargazer |date=2009-07-21|source=[[Reuters|Reuters]]|accessdate=2009-07-22 | first=Rob | last=Taylor}}</ref><ref name="Than">{{cite news|url=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2009/07/090721-jupiter-impact-spot.html|title=PHOTO: Jupiter Impact Creates Huge New Spot|last=Than|first=Ker|date=2009-07-21|publisher=[[National_Geographic|National Geographic]]|accessdate=2009-07-22}}</ref><ref name="Johnson">{{cite news|url=http://www.latimes.com/news/science/la-sci-jupiter22-2009jul22,0,5215362.story|title= 'Incredible' new scar is spreading on Jupiter|last=Johnson,  Jr.|first=John |publisher=[[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]]|accessdate=2009-07-22|date=2009-07-22}}</ref> --> 如果在撞击位置探测到水的存在则提示撞击物是彗星<ref name="perlman">Perlman, David. "[http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2009/07/23/MN5I18TT7U.DTL Glowing scar is revealing Jupiter's secrets] {{Wayback|url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=%2Fc%2Fa%2F2009%2F07%2F23%2FMN5I18TT7U.DTL |date=20120324213129 }}" ''San Francisco Chronicle, 23 July 2009.</ref>，相反则可能是[[小行星|小行星]]或非常小的[[木星卫星|卫星]]。<ref name="Grossman">{{cite news|url=http://www.newscientist.com/article/dn17491-jupiter-sports-new-bruise-from-impact.html|title=Jupiter sports new 'bruise' from impact|last=Grossman|first=Lisa|date=2009-07-21|publisher=[[New_Scientist|New Scientist]]|accessdate=2009-07-22|archive-date=2009-08-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090803010347/http://www.newscientist.com/article/dn17491-jupiter-sports-new-bruise-from-impact.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 起初，这次撞击事件的撞击物被认为更可能是一颗彗星，因为彗星更容易拥有行星穿越轨道。<ref name="Hergenrother">{{cite web |title=More on the Jupiter Impact |author=[http://transientsky.wordpress.com/about/ Carl Hergenrother] |url=http://transientsky.wordpress.com/2009/07/21/more-on-the-jupiter-impact/ |date=2009-07-21 |accessdate=2009-07-24 |archive-date=2016-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305154700/https://transientsky.wordpress.com/2009/07/21/more-on-the-jupiter-impact/ |dead-url=no }}</ref> 在木星的位置上（距离[[太阳|太阳]]5.2[[天文单位|天文单位]]），很多彗星由于离太阳距离远，性质不够活跃，很难被发现。<ref name="Hergenrother"/> 但在这个位置上，1千米级别的小型小行星同样也是很难被发现，最近奥顿等人和哈默尔等人的研究强烈提示这次撞击物是一颗小行星，因为这次撞击仅留下一个撞击点，而且撞击并没有减少木星磁层辐射出的十米波辐射，或产生高空二氧化硅尘埃碎片，这和苏梅克－列维9号彗星撞击事件很不相同。2012年，科学家确信这次撞击是由一颗直径为200－500米的小行星引起的。<ref name="PR2011">{{cite web
